<br>
<br>
How to use these mods:<br>
<br>
Installing and using a custom GUI Modification.<br>
<br>
1. Go to your &quot;.\EverQuest\uifiles&quot; directory and create a new directory.  Make the name of this directory the name you wish to give the mod.  (For this file, we'll call it UIMod)<br>
<br>
2. Go to your &quot;.\EverQuest\uifiles\default&quot; directory and copy all of the files in that directory to .\EverQuest\uifiles\UIMod.<br>
<br>
3. Unzip the files from the GUI Modification you wish to use into .\EverQuest\uifiles\UIMod    When it asks if you wish to replace files, click &quot;Yes to all.&quot;<br>
<br>
4. In game, type:   /loadskin UIMod   to load the skin.   You must zone once, or camp, for the Graphics files to take effects.  If you type  /loadskin UIMod 1  it will bring up the new UI without moving your windows.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Alternate Windows:<br>
CasterPlayerWindow        -Playerwindow, with mana.<br>
MeleePlayerwindow        -Playerwindow, blank mana bar space removed.<br>
<br>
DefaultPetInfoWindow        -Defailt Pet Info Window.<br>
QuickInvPW                -Changes the Pet Info Window into 8 inventory slots on four lines:                           Pri/Sec,  5/6,  Range/Ammo,   7/8     Very useful for keys, right                          click items, and frequesnt weapon switching.<br>
<br>
IconBuffWindow                -Changes the Buff Window back to Icons. <p><I>"Ohhh give me a home, where the Drolvarg don't roam... where the Tsu and the Urd Shamen play... Where seldom I'm trained, cuz I'm always feigned... and the Frenzy drops sashes alll dayyyyy...."</I> -Me, hugging dirt in PoF. <BR>
