<br>
I posted the instructions earlier in this thread, as well as in the GeistUI.txt file inside the zip.<br>
<br>
You need to be *SURE* that you Copy the WHOLE default diredtory to a DIFFERENT directory in the .\Everquest\uifiles directory.  If you copy a mod into default, the patcher will just over-write them.  If you copy just the files in the zip to their own directory, the Mod will not be able to load with the files from Default missing.  The UI Mods you download are NOT likely to contain all 131 files needed for a UI to work, just the few that were edited. <p><I>"Ohhh give me a home, where the Drolvarg don't roam... where the Tsu and the Urd Shamen play... Where seldom I'm trained, cuz I'm always feigned... and the Frenzy drops sashes alll dayyyyy...."</I> -Me, hugging dirt in PoF. <BR>
